    "As EPS increases, the threshold for grouping samples into the same cluster loosens, increasing average chunk size.",
    "As seen in Figure 3, this leads to a decrease in precision and an increase in recall for document and evidence retrieval, respectively, similar to the single-linkage case.",
    "As the distance threshold between consecutive sentences increases, fewer breakpoints appear, resulting in larger chunks.",
    "Regardless of the threshold type, it ultimately determines chunk size.",
    "In Figure 4, we observe similar trends to Figure 2 and 3: as chunk size increases, precision decreases in both retrieval tasks, while recall increases sharply for evidence retrieval."
